---

Peel and finely chop the @echalion shallot{1%large}(peeled and finely chopped) and grate the @garlic clove{1}(grated) (or use a #garlic press{} if you have one). Roughly chop the @chestnut mushrooms{1}(roughly chopped). Finely chop the @flat leaf parsley{½}(finely chopped). Bring a #pot{} of water to the boil for later.

Heat a splash of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} over high heat. Add your mushrooms in small batches and cook until they are golden brown, then remove from the pan and keep to one side. Add your shallot and garlic to the now empty pan and reduce the heat to medium-low. Cook for ~{3-4%minutes} until soft, if the pan gets too dry add a splash of water.

Return your mushrooms to the pan along with the @vegetable stock pot{½}, the @water{100%ml} (amount specified in the ingredient list) and a few good grinds of @black pepper{}. Allow to simmer over medium heat for ~{8-10%minutes} until thickened.

In another frying pan, heat a splash of oil on medium-high heat. When hot, add the @gnocchi{300%g}. Gently fry for ~{8%minutes} until it's crispy around the edges. Remove from the heat. Meanwhile, cut the @broccoli{1}(cut into small florets) into small florets. Plunge into the pot of boiling water for ~{3%minutes}, then remove, drain and keep to the side.

Stir the @creme fraiche{1} into your mushroom sauce. Once heated through, add your gnocchi and your broccoli and give it all a good stir. Taste for seasoning and add @salt{} and @black pepper{} as you wish.

Divide your mushroom and broccoli gnocchi between your #bowls{} and top with the @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g} and a sprinkling of your parsley.